  "datePublished": "2026-03-19",
  "description": "A Leitourgia is a quadruple (λ, φ, C, ι) — a designated agent in Hohfeldian liability position, a prescribed-form proposition, a witnessing community constituted by the gathering of compatible local witnesses, and a discharge proposition. Full discharge is joint settlement of two predicates: form-enactment (the act has been correctly performed) and forward-stability (the discharge carries forward into all continuations). The personal cost is the irreversible expenditure the leitourgos bears in performing the step that settles the discharge.",
